bbcode_text = "Kanban Tasks - Todo Manager is a simple kanban board integrated into the editor. It can be found in the \"Tasks\" main window.

Usage
- drag and drop tasks from one stage to another
- when you drag a task on the stage header it will be put at the beginning
- double click on names to change them (works on stages and tasks)
- use the details popup to enter a detailed description of the task

[b]Advanced[/b]
The board supports difftent categories and stages. At the moment these can not be configured from the plugin. Instead you have to open the [code]data.json[/code] file in the plugin directory. Extend the [code]categories[/code] entry to edit categories (There must be at least one category).
Use the [code]stages[/code] entry to add a new stage. To appear visualy the index of the stage has to be added to one column found in the [code]columns[/code] entry. Using this entry you can change the layout of the stages.
/!\\ editing the json can corrupt your file /!\\

[i]If you find a bug or want to suggest a new feature feel free to do so on Github.[/i]"
text = "Kanban Tasks - Todo Manager is a simple kanban board integrated into the editor. It can be found in the \"Tasks\" main window.

Usage
- drag and drop tasks from one stage to another
- when you drag a task on the stage header it will be put at the beginning
- double click on names to change them (works on stages and tasks)
- use the details popup to enter a detailed description of the task

Advanced
The board supports difftent categories and stages. At the moment these can not be configured from the plugin. Instead you have to open the data.json file in the plugin directory. Extend the categories entry to edit categories (There must be at least one category).
Use the stages entry to add a new stage. To appear visualy the index of the stage has to be added to one column found in the columns entry. Using this entry you can change the layout of the stages.
/!\\ editing the json can corrupt your file /!\\

If you find a bug or want to suggest a new feature feel free to do so on Github."

